                <head>Skirmish and Capture of Prisoners</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Imboden</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>General</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Two companies of Imboden's Cavalry attacked the enemy at Burnt House, about
                    seven miles from Beverly, and captured thirty-eight horses and thirty-seven
                    Yankees. The prisoners passed through Staunton on their way to Richmond.</summary>
                <note/>
