                <summary>At the large gathering of Augusta citizens on Monday, September 28, a
                    committee was appointed to write resolutions which were unanimously adopted
                    following the speeches by Generals Wigfall and Smith. The Honorable A. H. H.
                    Stuart was appointed chairman, and A. F. Kinney was appointed secretary of the
                    assembly. Thomas J. Michie, Benjamin Crawford, and Matthew Pilson were appointed
                    to a committee to host the speakers. Thomas J. Michie, Major S. L. Lewis, Jacob
                    Baylor, Samuel B. Finley, William P. Tate, J. Marshall McCue, Dr. John
                    McChesney, A. Koiner, and John S. Ellis were appointed to the resolutions
                    committee. N. C. Trout and S. B. Finley offered other motions. The resolutions
                    thank the women of the county for their patriotic service, discourage desertion
                    by soldiers, and encourage citizens both to pay the tithe of produce as tax and
                    to abide by prices set by the government for surplus produce.</summary>
